BCR adjustments to icu4c/source/common/BUILD.bazel.

Inherited from 78.2.bcr.1:

* :platform — replace upstream's explicit srcs list with
  `glob(*.h, *.cpp)`; wire in `@icu_dat` via `data` + `@rules_cc//cc/runfiles`
  + `ICU_DATA_DIR_BAZEL=$(rlocationpath @icu_dat)` so the static
  library can locate its `icudt78l.dat` at runtime; gate the historical
  `-ldl` linkopt to Linux only.

New in 78.2.bcr.2 (MSVC build fixes):

* :headers — propagate `U_STATIC_IMPLEMENTATION` to consumers via
  `defines` on MSVC. Without it, icu's public headers emit
  `__declspec(dllimport)` references that the static-link build
  cannot satisfy (LNK4217 / LNK1120 "imported but not defined").
  GCC/clang/MinGW unaffected.

* :platform — `/utf-8` copts on MSVC: globbed sources include UTF-8
  char literals (e.g. static_unicode_sets currency symbols) that
  MSVC misreads as multi-byte char constants (C2015) without the flag.

* :uchar — `/utf-8` copts on MSVC. uchar.cpp's fullwidth-letter
  literals (u'ａ' etc.) hit the same C2015.

